body:
The library has problem to release memory on row.commit() if there is a previous worksheet that is not commited. By "previous" I mean worksheet with lower index.

I have process that fetches data page by page. Based on every page I write data to all worksheets, so I cannot commit worksheet before I write all data from all pages. That leads to memory issue on a server.

I have created sample app, that shows the problem. 
https://github.com/Wafel/ExcelJSMemoryIssue
In readme there is full description and screenshots from memory profiler. 

Here is piece of code that creates few worksheets and writes data to it.
It's works fine until I remove `PROBLEMATIC LINE`. If I remove `PROBLEMATIC LINE` then memory is released only from first worksheet and all next worksheets leads to memory issue.
```
const options = {
    filename: `test-${new Date().getTime()}.xlsx`
};
const workbook = new Excel.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter(options);

const sheetsCount = parseInt(req.query.sheetsCount) || 3;
const columnsCount = parseInt(req.query.columnsCount) || 10;
const rowsCount = parseInt(req.query.rowsCount) || 1000000;

_.range(sheetsCount).forEach(sheetIndex => workbook.addWorksheet(`Sheet ${sheetIndex}`));

for (let sheetIndex = 1; sheetIndex <= sheetsCount; sheetIndex++) {

    let worksheet = workbook.getWorksheet(sheetIndex);

    for (let rowIndex = 0; rowIndex < rowsCount; rowIndex++) {
        worksheet.addRow(_.range(columnsCount)).commit();
        await setImmediatePromise();
    }

    worksheet.commit(); // PROBLEMATIC LINE
}

await workbook.commit();
```

Please tell me if there is any chance that it will be fixed.
